name: HD 89345
scenarioDescription:
The HD 89345 Exoplanetary System


Overview

HD 89345 is a star with 1.16 times the mass of the Sun, and 1.75 times its radius. It is located 433.14 light years away from the solar system and is estimated to be 7.53 billion years old, as compared to the Sun which is roughly 4.6 billion years old.

HD 89345 is known to have 1 exoplanets in orbit around it.


Exoplanets in the HD 89345 system


HD 89345 b

HD 89345 b was discovered by the K2 observatory using the transit method. Its semi-major axis is 0.11 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of HD 89345 b is 34.98 times the mass of Earth. The radius of HD 89345 b is 7.398 that of Earth. At more than 10 Earth masses, HD 89345 b is an ice giant, a planet that is made up mostly of volatiles like water, amonia and methane, and enveloped by a dense hydrogen and helium atmosphere, much like Uranus and Neptune in our solar system.
description: 3D visualisation and gravity simulation of the exoplanet system HD 89345, which contains 1 planets and was discovered by K2.
